   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 6  FastText (Bojanowski et al., Facebook AI, 2017)\n",
    "\n",
    "Both Word2Vec and GloVe treat each word as an **atomic unit**.  \n",
    "They fail on:\n",
    "- **Out-of-vocabulary (OOV) words** (unseen during training)\n",
    "- **Morphologically rich languages** (German, Finnish, Turkish, ...)\n",
    "\n",
    "**FastText** solves this by representing each word as a **bag of character n-grams**.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Example\n",
    "\n",
    "Word: `\"running\"` with n=3 and boundary markers `<`, `>`:\n",
    "```\n",
    "n-grams: <ru  run  unn  nni  nin  ing  ng>\n",
    "         <running>   ← full word as its own n-gram\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "The word embedding is the **sum** of its n-gram embeddings.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Benefits\n",
    "| Feature | Effect |\n",
    "|---------|--------|\n",
    "| Character n-grams | Handles OOV words at inference time |\n",
    "| Morphological awareness | Better on inflected languages |\n",
    "| Rare word coverage | Even hapax legomena get decent vectors |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Demonstrate n-gram decomposition\n",
    "def get_ngrams(word, n_min=3, n_max=6, add_boundary=True):\n",
    "    if add_boundary:\n",
    "        word = f'<{word}>'\n",
    "    ngrams = set()\n",
    "    for n in range(n_min, n_max + 1):\n",
    "        for i in range(len(word) - n + 1):\n",
    "            ngrams.add(word[i:i+n])\n",
    "    return sorted(ngrams)\n",
    "\n",
    "for word in ['running', 'run', 'runner', 'sprint']:\n",
    "    ngrams = get_ngrams(word)\n",
    "    print(f'{word:<10} → {ngrams}')\n",
    "\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('\"sprint\" is OOV for Word2Vec, but FastText can still embed it')\n",
    "print('using shared n-grams with \"sprinting\", \"sprinted\", etc.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Train a FastText model with Gensim\n",
    "from gensim.models import FastText\n",
    "\n",
    "ft_model = FastText(\n",
    "    sentences,\n",
    "    vector_size=50,\n",
    "    window=3,\n",
    "    min_count=1,\n",
    "    min_n=3,      # minimum n-gram length\n",
    "    max_n=6,      # maximum n-gram length\n",
    "    epochs=300,\n",
    "    seed=42,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print('FastText model trained.')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "# OOV demo — 'kings' was not in training corpus\n",
    "oov_word = 'kingdoms'\n",
    "print(f'Most similar to \"{oov_word}\" (OOV word):')\n",
    "for w, s in ft_model.wv.most_similar(oov_word, topn=5):\n",
    "    print(f'  {w:<12} {s:.3f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 7  Evaluating Embeddings\n",
    "\n",
    "Two main evaluation paradigms:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Type | Task | Example |\n",
    "|------|------|---------|\n",
    "| **Intrinsic** | Word similarity | SimLex-999, WordSim-353 |\n",
    "| **Intrinsic** | Analogies | *king:queen :: man:?* |\n",
    "| **Extrinsic** | Downstream task | NER, sentiment, POS tagging |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Word Similarity\n",
    "Compare model cosine similarity to human judgement scores.\n",
    "High Spearman correlation = good model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from scipy.stats import spearmanr\n",
    "\n",
    "# Toy similarity benchmark (human judgements on a 0–1 scale)\n",
    "human_scores = {\n",
    "    ('king',  'queen'):  0.95,\n",
    "    ('king',  'prince'): 0.78,\n",
    "    ('man',   'woman'):  0.85,\n",
    "    ('dog',   'cat'):    0.82,\n",
    "    ('paris', 'berlin'): 0.75,\n",
    "    ('king',  'dog'):    0.10,\n",
    "    ('paris', 'dog'):    0.05,\n",
    "    ('man',   'dog'):    0.25,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "human  = []\n",
    "model_ = []\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"{'Pair':<25} {'Human':>7} {'SG':>7} {'CBOW':>7} {'FT':>7}\")\n",
    "print('-' * 58)\n",
    "for (w1, w2), h_score in human_scores.items():\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        sg_s   = model_sg.wv.similarity(w1, w2)\n",
    "        cbow_s = model_cbow.wv.similarity(w1, w2)\n",
    "        ft_s   = ft_model.wv.similarity(w1, w2)\n",
    "        human.append(h_score)\n",
    "        model_.append(sg_s)\n",
    "        print(f'{w1} ↔ {w2:<18} {h_score:>7.2f} {sg_s:>7.3f} {cbow_s:>7.3f} {ft_s:>7.3f}')\n",
    "    except KeyError as e:\n",
    "        print(f'  {e} not in vocabulary')\n",
    "\n",
    "rho, p = spearmanr(human, model_)\n",
    "print(f'\\nSpearman ρ (Skip-gram vs human): {rho:.3f}  (p={p:.3f})')\n",
    "print('Note: ρ ≈ 0.7–0.8 is typical for well-trained embeddings on real benchmarks.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 8  Visualising Embedding Space with t-SNE\n",
    "\n",
    "Embeddings live in *d*-dimensional space (e.g. 50D). We can't see that.  \n",
    "**t-SNE** (t-distributed Stochastic Neighbour Embedding) reduces to 2D while  \n",
    "preserving **local neighbourhood structure** (nearby words stay nearby)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.manifold import TSNE\n",
    "\n",
    "# Select a meaningful subset of words\n",
    "groups = {\n",
    "    'Royalty':    ['king', 'queen', 'prince', 'princess'],\n",
    "    'Capitals':   ['paris', 'berlin', 'rome', 'london'],\n",
    "    'Countries':  ['france', 'germany', 'italy', 'england'],\n",
    "    'Animals':    ['dog', 'cat'],\n",
    "    'People':     ['man', 'woman'],\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "words = [w for ws in groups.values() for w in ws]\n",
    "available = [w for w in words if w in model_sg.wv]\n",
    "\n",
    "vectors = np.array([model_sg.wv[w] for w in available])\n",
    "\n",
    "tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, perplexity=min(5, len(available)-1),\n",
    "            random_state=42, n_iter=2000)\n",
    "coords = tsne.fit_transform(vectors)\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Plot ---\n",
    "colors = ['#e63946', '#457b9d', '#2a9d8f', '#e9c46a', '#f4a261']\n",
    "group_names = list(groups.keys())\n",
    "word_to_group = {w: g for g, ws in groups.items() for w in ws}\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 6))\n",
    "ax.set_facecolor('#f8f9fa')\n",
    "ax.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, word in enumerate(available):\n",
    "    group = word_to_group.get(word, 'Other')\n",
    "    gidx  = group_names.index(group) if group in group_names else -1\n",
    "    color = colors[gidx % len(colors)]\n",
    "    ax.scatter(coords[i, 0], coords[i, 1], color=color, s=90, zorder=3)\n",
    "    ax.annotate(word, (coords[i, 0], coords[i, 1]),\n",
    "                fontsize=11, xytext=(5, 5), textcoords='offset points')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Legend\n",
    "from matplotlib.lines import Line2D\n",
    "handles = [Line2D([0],[0], marker='o', color='w', markerfacecolor=colors[i], markersize=10,\n",
    "                  label=name)\n",
    "           for i, name in enumerate(group_names)]\n",
    "ax.legend(handles=handles, loc='best', framealpha=0.9)\n",
    "ax.set_title('t-SNE visualisation of Word2Vec (Skip-gram) embeddings', fontsize=13)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('t-SNE dim 1')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('t-SNE dim 2')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('tsne_embeddings.png', dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print('Words from the same semantic group should cluster together.')"
   ]
  },
