    "---\n",
    "## 9  Static vs Contextual Embeddings — A Bridge to Modern NLP\n",
    "\n",
    "All methods covered so far produce **static** embeddings:  \n",
    "every occurrence of a word gets **one fixed vector**, regardless of context.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "\"I went to the bank to deposit money.\"    → bank = [0.12, -0.34, ...]\n",
    "\"The river bank was covered in mud.\"      → bank = [0.12, -0.34, ...]  ← same!\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the **polysemy problem**.  Modern models solve it with **contextual embeddings**:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Model | Year | Key idea |\n",
    "|-------|------|----------|\n",
    "| ELMo  | 2018 | Bidirectional LSTMs; context-dependent vectors |\n",
    "| BERT  | 2018 | Transformer encoders; deep bidirectional context |\n",
    "| GPT   | 2018+ | Transformer decoders; left-to-right context |\n",
    "\n",
    "**But static embeddings still matter:**\n",
    "- Fast and memory-efficient at inference\n",
    "- Excellent for keyword-search, information retrieval\n",
    "- Interpretable and easy to analyse\n",
    "- Foundation for understanding *why* contextual models work"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Summary table\n",
    "summary = [\n",
    "    ('Method',      'Type',          'OOV?', 'Corpus use',     'Typical dim', 'Year'),\n",
    "    ('One-hot',     'Count',         'No',   'Vocabulary',     'V (sparse)',  '—'),\n",
    "    ('PPMI',        'Count',         'No',   'Co-occurrence',  'V (sparse)',  '≤2002'),\n",
    "    ('Word2Vec SG', 'Predict (NN)',  'No',   'Local window',   '100–300',     '2013'),\n",
    "    ('Word2Vec CB', 'Predict (NN)',  'No',   'Local window',   '100–300',     '2013'),\n",
    "    ('GloVe',       'Factorisation', 'No',   'Global matrix',  '50–300',      '2014'),\n",
    "    ('FastText',    'Predict (NN)',  'YES',  'Local + n-gram', '100–300',     '2017'),\n",
    "    ('ELMo',        'Contextual',   'YES',  'Whole sentence', '512–1024',    '2018'),\n",
    "    ('BERT',        'Contextual',   'YES',  'Whole sentence', '768',         '2018'),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "header = summary[0]\n",
    "rows   = summary[1:]\n",
    "widths = [max(len(r[i]) for r in summary) + 2 for i in range(len(header))]\n",
    "\n",
    "def fmt_row(row):\n",
    "    return '  '.join(cell.ljust(w) for cell, w in zip(row, widths))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(fmt_row(header))\n",
    "print('─' * sum(widths + [2] * len(widths)))\n",
    "for row in rows:\n",
    "    print(fmt_row(row))"
   ]
